doc.ContractDescription: HERO TWIN ASTRONAUT STUDY CONSORTIUM (TASC) PROJECT: COGNITION ON MONOZYGOTIC TWIN ON EARTH THIS PROPOSAL FOCUSES ON RESEARCH EMPHASIS 8 OF APPENDIX D OF THE TWINS SOLICITATION: PSYCHOSOCIAL AND NEUROBEHAVIORAL EXPERIMENTS TO INVESTIGATIVE AND CHARACTERIZE ANY DIFFERENCES BETWEEN SCOTT AND MARK KELLY IN COGNITION, DECISION MAKING ABILITY, ALERTNESS LEVELS, STRESS, AND OVERALL EMOTIONAL WELL-BEING, AS A RESULT OF THE SPACEFLIGHT ENVIRONMENT. IT IS PART OF THE NASA HERO TWIN ASTRONAUTS SPACEFLIGHT CONSORTIA, WHICH SEEK TO INTEGRATE -OMICS STUDIES ON THE EFFECTS OF SPACEFLIGHT VIA COLLABORATION, DATA-SHARING, AND DATA ANALYSES RELATIVE TO NEUROBEHAVIORAL AND PSYCHOSOCIAL ASSESSMENTS OF THE TWINS. WE WILL ASSESS COGNITIVE PERFORMANCE IN THE TWINS WITH THE COGNITION TEST BATTERY 3 TIMES PRE-, 11 TIMES IN-, AND 3 TIMES POST-FLIGHT. COGNITION WAS SPECIFICALLY DEVELOPED FOR HIGH-PERFORMING ASTRONAUTS AND CONSISTS OF 10 BRIEF, VALIDATED NEUROPSYCHOLOGICAL TESTS THAT COVER A WIDE RANGE OF COGNITIVE DOMAINS. THE PROJECT'S SPECIFIC AIMS SERVE TO DETERMINE HOW COGNITIVE ASPECTS OF SCOTT KELLY'S PHENOTYPE CHANGE IN RESPONSE TO ACUTE AND PROLONGED EXPOSURE TO MICROGRAVITY AND OTHER SPACEFLIGHT STRESSORS, BOTH ON A WITHIN-SUBJECT LEVEL (E.G., IN-FLIGHT VS. PRE-FLIGHT) AND ON A BETWEEN-SUBJECTS LEVEL (I.E., IN COMPARISON TO MARK'S DATA). THESE PHENOTYPIC DATA WILL BE SHARED WITHIN AND OUTSIDE THE CONSORTIUM AND CORRELATED WITH FINDINGS FROM THE -OMICS ANALYSES.
